@startuml AddItemsToOrder
title Add Items to Order Flow

actor "Kitchen\nTablet" as Tablet
participant "API\nGateway" as Gateway
participant "Order\nService" as OS
participant "Menu\nService" as MS
database "Order DB" as ODB

Tablet -> Gateway: POST /orders/{orderId}/items\n{menuItemId, quantity: 2}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> OS: Forward request
activate OS

OS -> MS: GET /menus/{menuId}/items/{itemId}
activate MS
MS --> OS: MenuItem{name, price: 7.50, available: true}
deactivate MS

note over OS
  Validation:
  - Item exists ✓
  - Item available ✓  
  - Menu active ✓
  - Calculate: 7.50 × 2 = 15.00
end note

OS -> ODB: ADD OrderItem\nUpdate Order.totalPrice
activate ODB
ODB --> OS: OrderItem{id, quantity, unitPrice, status}
deactivate ODB

OS --> Gateway: HTTP 201 Created
deactivate OS
Gateway --> Tablet: OrderItem response
deactivate Gateway
@enduml
